(50, 110, 'Luke Fraser', 'thebombadils@gmail.com', 'http://www.thebombadils.com', '69.159.141.49', '2013-04-17 18:22:14', '2013-04-17 22:22:14', 'Just played a gig here, Feb 2013. The soundman JT is awesome. He does all the sound from his ipad and is right up on stage with you getting the sound just perfect. Nice big room. Great ambiance. Highly rated. Apparently they host more live shows than any other venue in Canada. Apparently over 400 shows per year.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:20.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/20.0', '', 0, 0),
(4, 85, 'rjfrizz', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 13:52:07', '2013-01-13 18:52:07', 'This is a great new venue!  If you do an acoustic/jazz sort of thing these guys will treat you right.  For now they have a minimal sound system, but it does the trick for most jazz based groups.  The cafe serves great food and coffee, and some alcoholic drinks.  Everything reasonably priced.  People love to go and hang out at Resonance, so there''s a bit of a built in audience.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(5, 49, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 13:57:40', '2013-01-13 18:57:40', 'Il Motore is a good venue with good sound.  It''s a bit out of the way, as it''s up in a part of the city that doesn''t get much foot traffic.  But it''s got a cool vibe.  A lot of the shows there are booked through a promoter, I believe, but it''s a good bet for a band with a decent draw in Montreal.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(6, 51, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:01:12', '2013-01-13 19:01:12', 'Pretty good sound.  You have to pay for the room, I don''t remember how much.  But it''s pretty big, so if you have a good draw in Montreal it might suit you.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(51, 172, 'Gern f.', 'gern@uswm.ca', '', '173.178.174.33', '2013-04-18 12:33:33', '2013-04-18 16:33:33', 'Old man bar/brasserie that has been taken over by young hip anarchist, they do a good job of getting the word out about shows. The sound is pretty good, merch sales are great, we''ve had some good shows here, probably one of the best places to play in Quebec if you haven''t played there before. I think any folk, country, roots, rock and singer songwriter stuff would fly here.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; rv:16.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/16.0', '', 0, 0),
(8, 44, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:08:29', '2013-01-13 19:08:29', 'Small stage, but I''ve seen it fit 6 people squished.  It''s not really a stage either, it''s elevated about half a foot off the ground.  But don''t get me wrong, this is one of Montreal''s better venues for touring bands, it has a great dirty rock vibe.  In the summer people love to sit on the terrasse they have in the front (and the back).  It''s pretty small, but fun.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(9, 43, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:11:11', '2013-01-13 19:11:11', 'It''s pretty much next door to L''esco.  It''s an alright place to play.  The bar is reasonably big.  They have some "regulars" who like to sit at the back and drink.  I don''t remember what they do for beer deals, or door for that matter.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(10, 42, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:15:08', '2013-01-13 19:15:08', 'Divan can be a bit of a gamble in terms of sound... but it''s really a cool place, one of the best in Montreal.  It''s located in the plateau, and they get a bit of foot traffic, so sometimes people will just wander in off the street. They host live shows every night of the week.  The staff are awesome and helpful.  As I recall, I think you pay for the sound guy and keep the door.  Recommended!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(11, 39, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:18:49', '2013-01-13 19:18:49', 'Probably the best small bar/venue in Montreal.  They''re devoted to putting on shows for local and touring bands.  It has a great vibe and good beer, cheap whisky.  Ever since they opened the room next door for shows it has worked perfectly.  They host a lot of indie/rock with a good dose of experimental and free jazz.  Really the best...', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(12, 41, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:22:48', '2013-01-13 19:22:48', 'This is the big brother to Casa del Popolo, and is located across the street.  It''s a bigger venue, but if you can fill it, it''s worth it.  Sala is a beautiful room, great bar, good sound.  What more is there to say? This is the best place to see and play a show.  Might be tough to book.  If you wanna book Sala, book early.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(13, 7, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:27:08', '2013-01-13 19:27:08', 'Cagibi is pretty cool, they recently upgraded their sound system, and are looking to push the room as more of a "venue" where as... say last year, it was more of a cafe, with lots of experimental art.  But that comes at a price, you pay for the sound/rental now at cagibi, but as a result, it''s infinitely better than it used to be.  It''s a small room, but cool.  You have to wrap it up by midnight.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(14, 40, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '74.116.189.206', '2013-01-13 14:36:11', '2013-01-13 19:36:11', 'When we came through Edmonton with Bent By Elephants, this show was really a highlight of the tour.  Craig and the guys at Wunderbar are doing great things for music in Edmonton.  There''s no sound guy, they do it themselves, but they still managed to work it out for our band, which was by no means simple.  They have great beer and they are generous to bands with it.  As I recall, bands keep the door money.  It''s a small room but a great vibe.  Absolutely recommended.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.101 Safari/537.11', '', 0, 1),
(101, 415, 'Katie Turvill', 'katie.turvill@gmail.com', 'http://www.roxyvan.com', '96.49.137.40', '2013-06-10 16:00:00', '2013-06-10 20:00:00', 'I am the social media manager for the Roxy and I was wondering if it was possible to add pictures to this listing as well. Or if you need any more information from us.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:21.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/21.0', '', 0, 0),
(102, 415, 'Ryan', 'rjfrizz@gmail.com', 'http://35', '173.246.6.3', '2013-06-10 16:06:45', '2013-06-10 20:06:45', 'Hi Katie,\r\nFeel free to add photos using the "choose file" button located above the map.  You can submit the capacity of the venue using the "edit venue" section.  If you have information about the technical specifications or door deals you can submit them in the "edit venue" section as well.  \r\nThanks for your comment and contributions.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_3) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/27.0.1453.110 Safari/537.36', '', 101, 1),
(17, 159, '', '', '', '50.68.35.249', '2013-02-07 12:47:03', '2013-02-07 17:47:03', 'The Railway club is a Vancouver staple. It''s small, narrow but has a lot of charm. Staff is friendly, sound system is good.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 0, 0),
(18, 70, 'KJ', '', '', '50.68.35.249', '2013-02-07 12:51:47', '2013-02-07 17:51:47', 'This venue is great. Recently renovated, elevated stage, 2nd bar, bigger capacity. Owners are awesome.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 0, 0),
(19, 116, 'KJ', '', '', '50.68.35.249', '2013-02-07 12:54:17', '2013-02-07 17:54:17', 'This venue is great! It''s at risk of being shut down, so play here while you can! Owners are amazing and truly love live music. Sound man Guy is a little rough around the edges, but you''ll have the best sound on your Western Canadian tour guaranteed. Great food, great room, and they can put you up for the night really cheap at a great hotel.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 0, 0),
(28, 205, 'Djam Bass', 'djambass@gmail.com', 'http://NA', '96.51.76.95', '2013-03-08 20:33:58', '2013-03-09 01:33:58', 'Great venue to play, the owner is a professional musician. Stage and sight lines are good.  Music '' days a week.  Bass Amp, Drums, PA.  Not a huge stage though workable 4 and 5 possible people possible. \r\nSound:   It is a good sounding room. Bass throws, volume is a non-issue, PA is good. \r\nOne surprise sonically is on stage there are a few large bass standing waves, stage is a  bass heavy. Easy work around.   Other than that this is much better than most rooms to perform in a informal setting.  \r\n\r\nIt is a Saloon, unpretentious vibe without ` problem or issues`.  \r\n\r\nDid I mention LIVE  Music 7 days a week? \r\nThe owner (Musician) is wonderful.\r\n\r\nHope this helps.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:19.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/19.0', '', 0, 0),
(22, 41, 'Gern f.', 'gern@uswm.ca', '', '69.157.173.172', '2013-02-21 22:00:09', '2013-02-22 03:00:09', 'Ya Sala is the place to play, I''ve a;ways found the sound to be a little dodgie, but workable. The room is a great size, fits a ton of folks, but will work if only 75 people show. Yes 75, maybe 50 if it is your mark. The cool part about this place is that folks love to see bands here, so you can expect to have more than your average amount of people show up just cause it is at Sala, the room does draw. Its a great place for your bigger shows for bands that have a Montreal draw, down side is that it books real early, I''d say 4 or 5 months out if there is a specific date you are looking for. As well there is a room rental involved but have found it works out in your favour because you can charge more at the door, and fit more people, cause it''s Sala. This is the best large room rate in Montreal easy. We have played our best and most memorable shows in this room, can''t wait to do it again.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 0, 0),
(23, 44, 'Gern f.', 'gern@uswm.ca', '', '69.157.173.172', '2013-02-21 22:06:57', '2013-02-22 03:06:57', 'This is a great gritty little club. It has a big old sound system for a small place, the stage is low, the ceiling is low, but it''s the kind of place were you can get right in the face of your audiance. It''s located right on the main drag and they have alot of shows, so a fair amount of street traffic and built in crowd. You aren''t gonna get ritch playing here but it''s a great place for a show. As well it''s a great cross over club between the french and english scenes, probably the best venue to get seen by the francophone kids.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 0, 0),
(24, 44, 'Gern f.', 'gern@uswm.ca', '', '69.157.173.172', '2013-02-21 22:13:33', '2013-02-22 03:13:33', 'Oh yah, the load in is teribble, there is never any parking, and never, like every venue in all of Montreal, ever leave anything of value in your van!, Ever, it will get ripped off, they will break your windows to see if you have done your laundry. Load in as soon as you get there and use the venues lock up or leave some one in your van. This is not to freak you out about L''esco, this is too freak you out about every venue in Montreal, there are crews awaiting to rip off your gear and luggage, and that plastic Jesus on your dash, empty vans remain empty.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8) AppleWebKit/534.50.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.6 Safari/533.22.3', '', 23, 0),
