(75, 1, '2012-11-30 12:35:00', '2012-11-30 17:35:00', '\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\nHow To Book A Show At Phog\r\n<br>\r\nE-mail Tom Lucier at phoglounge@gmail.com with several potential dates that you’re hoping to book. Your first choice may not be available\r\n<br>\r\nIn the event that the best night for your gig is booked, you can search the line-ups upcoming on www.phoglounge.com and check if you fit any shows happening in the next two months.\r\n<br>\r\nThere are hyperlinks to all the performers so you can listen and check if your sound works with the show already booked.\r\n<br>\r\nAnything with only two bands, or a TBA, potentially has room for an opening set. Mostly though…we’d prefer one out of town band and one local…or just a couple of locals.\r\n<br>\r\nThe best way to book a show is to have a local (or two) already slated to join you on the show. This is the simplest set-up for Phog to begin promoting the show quickly instead of hunting for local bands available for your show.\r\n<br>\r\nFor more info about what happens after you book a show, read <a href="http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/">“FAQs for Bands Booked at Phog”.</a>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n------------------------\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/">http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/</a>\r\n', 'Phog Lounge', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'phog-lounge', '', '', '2013-04-26 12:37:08', '2013-04-26 16:37:08', '', 0, 'http://stagebanter.ca/?post_type=venues&#038;p=75', 0, 'venues', '', 0),
