(280, 1, '2013-04-29 11:47:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<h3>This is not a music review website.  I''m not a writer.</h3>\nIn fact, one of the things I like about the StageBanter is that it is, in a way, democratic (or tries to be anyway). It doesn''t make any decisions about what kind of music gets shared, heard, or promoted. Instead it offers musicians a tool to promote and share their own music. And hopefully leaves the choice of what music to listen to or buy up to the listener. (Please, note that I realize that StageBanter falls short in this respect in some ways: translation to french is a feature to be added soon, the venues listed are mostly indie venues, but only because those are the venues that I am familiar with. We want to add all types of venues to serve all genres of music.)\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI never wanted to be in a position of reviewing music, claiming that one kind of music is better or more deserving of public attention than another. But alas, I have found myself in that position already... in the very infancy of this site''s existance, I have had to make some of those kinds of decisions. For instance, I''m very excited to present the StageBanter launch show on <strong><a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/131453790360354/" target="_blank">March 12 at Sala Rossa</a></strong>. But this was a show to promote StageBanter, and I wanted to present music that I like, so I could get excited about it and do a better job promoting it.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://stagebanter.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/StageBanter-poster-e1361209491729.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-266 aligncenter" alt="StageBanter.ca event poster" src="http://stagebanter.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/StageBanter-poster-e1361827080290.png" width="200" height="309" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSo I got my own band on board, <a href="http://bentbyelephantsband.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Bent By Elephants</a>. And I became respectfully obsessed with the music of <a href="http://aldenpenner.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Alden Penner</a>, so I was very excited to find out that he was interested in presenting a project. And I wanted a band that would fit the style and had done some significant Canadian touring. I thought of <a href="http://erinlang.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Erin Lang</a>, because we hadn''t played together before, and she does amazing work.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nJust by choosing these bands I was deciding which music to promote.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nI also offer an option in the <a href="http://stagebanter.ca/add-a-venue/" target="_blank">"Add A Venue"</a> form where I tweet about bands that submit venues. This is supposed to serve as an incentive, but perhaps isn''t very enticing at the moment given my limited number of twitter followers (44 at the time of this post). But hey, you do what you can. So in most cases, if a band requests a tweet it will be more along the lines of "Band X is helping to promote live music in Canada! check out their music at bandbandband.bandcamp.com."  Sort of a way to stimulate connections between bands and to help them get their music out.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBut there is a one case in particular that I''m inclined to give a little more notice to than usual.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Welcome/Launch/AlexanderPWhyte', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-04-29 11:47:10', '2013-04-29 15:47:10', '', 0, 'http://stagebanter.ca/?p=280', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(281, 1, '2013-02-25 16:27:29', '2013-02-25 21:27:29', '<h3>This is not a music review website.  I''m not a writer.</h3>\nIn fact, one of the things I like about the StageBanter is that it is, in a way, democratic (or tries to be anyway). It doesn''t make any decisions about what kind of music gets shared, heard, or promoted. Instead it offers musicians a tool to promote and share their own music. And hopefully leaves the choice of what music to listen to or buy up to the listener. (Please, note that I realize that StageBanter falls short in this respect in some ways: translation to french is a feature to be added soon, the venues listed are mostly indie venues, but only because those are the venues that I am familiar with. We want to add all types of venues to serve all genres of music.)\n\nI never wanted to be in a position of reviewing music, claiming that one kind of music is better or more deserving of public attention than another. But alas, I have found myself in that position already... in the very infancy of this site''s existance, I have had to make some of those kinds of decisions. For instance, I''m very excited to present the StageBanter launch show on <strong><a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/131453790360354/" target="_blank">March 12 at Sala Rossa</a></strong>. But this was a show to promote StageBanter, and I wanted to present music that I like, so I could get excited about it and do a better job promoting it.\n\n<a href="http://stagebanter.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/StageBanter-poster-e1361209491729.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-266 aligncenter" alt="StageBanter.ca event poster" src="http://stagebanter.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/StageBanter-poster-e1361827080290.png" width="200" height="309" /></a>\n\nSo I got my own band on board, <a href="http://bentbyelephantsband.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Bent By Elephants</a>. And I became respectfully obsessed with the music of <a href="http://aldenpenner.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Alden Penner</a>, so I was very excited to find out that he was interested in presenting a project. And I wanted a band that would fit the style and had done some significant Canadian touring. I thought of <a href="http://erinlang.bandcamp.com" target="_blank">Erin Lang</a>, because we hadn''t played together before, and she does amazing work.\n\nI also offer an option in the <a href="http://stagebanter.ca/add-a-venue/" target="_blank">"Add A Venue"</a> form where I tweet about bands that submit venues.  This is supposed to serve as an incentive, but perhaps isn''t very enticing at the moment given my limited number of twitter followers (44 at the time of this post).  But hey you do what you can.  So in most cases, if a band requests a tweet it will be more along the lines of "Band X is helping to promote live music in Canada! check out their music at bandbandband.bandcamp.c', 'Welcome/Launch/AlexanderPWhyte', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '280-revision', '', '', '2013-02-25 16:27:29', '2013-02-25 21:27:29', '', 280, 'http://stagebanter.ca/news/280-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
