(358, 1, '2013-04-16 11:42:06', '2013-04-16 15:42:06', '"Established 1989, with its name taken from a Clash song, Jimmy Jazz, Guelph, features live entertainment almost every night of the week. Sundays host one of the most popular Open Stage Nights in the city, hosted by local musician Nate Coles. Mondays feature Skydiggers guitarist and Tri-City legend Paul MacLeod. Wellington Breweries, Trailhead Trivia Tuesdays and Name That Tune Wednesdays, are also weekly staples. The rest of the week can be filled by local, Guelph musicians or guests from abroad.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nJimmy Jazz has one of the most diverse musical palettes in Guelph, a patio that’s heated and open year round and a friendly body of regulars that will keep you coming back.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHours of Operation\nOpen 8pm to 2am everyday"\n\n&nbsp;\n\nSource: <a href="http://www.musiclives.ca/venues/jimmy-jazz/">http://www.musiclives.ca/venues/jimmy-jazz/</a>', 'Jimmy Jazz', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '340-autosave', '', '', '2013-04-16 11:42:06', '2013-04-16 15:42:06', '', 340, 'http://stagebanter.ca/news/340-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(359, 1, '2013-04-16 12:38:48', '2013-04-16 16:38:48', '"The Albion Hotel and Wellington Brewery proudly support independent musicians and their efforts to bring their music to the world. The Albion stage features indie acts that range from up and coming talent just starting their musical journey, to signed and recorded artists.\nOur Independent Music Series showcases both local and touring bands and artists- If you would like more information on how to inquire about bookings, please contact:info@thealbionhotel.ca"\n\nSource: <a href="http://www.thealbionhotel.ca/default.asp?id=6&amp;l=1">http://www.thealbionhotel.ca/default.asp?id=6&amp;l=1</a>', 'The Albion Hotel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '338-autosave', '', '', '2013-04-16 12:38:48', '2013-04-16 16:38:48', '', 338, 'http://stagebanter.ca/news/338-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
