(462, 19, '2013-07-15 13:15:07', '2013-07-15 17:15:07', 'Hi, Ryan. Thank you for the above information. I was wondering if I could ask you a couple of questions regarding the music scene in Canada. Are there a lot of venues/opportunities for new bands to play and promote their music? Do all bands need a promoter/manager to get these kind of opportunities? Or the venues have some catch like selling tickets or something in order to play there? I live in Mexico and I have a new project but all songs are in english so we are considering going to Canada and try to promote ourselves out there. We have a lot to consider to make our next move so any information you could provide will be greatly appreciated. Here''s the link of the project in case you are interested: www.reverbnation.com/somekindofthree \n\nThanks in advance,\n\nErick C.', 'Reply To: Montreal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'reply-to-montreal', '', '', '2013-07-15 13:15:07', '2013-07-15 17:15:07', '', 456, 'http://stagebanter.ca/forums/reply/reply-to-montreal/', 1, 'reply', '', 0),
