(466, 19, '2013-07-27 17:46:23', '2013-07-27 21:46:23', 'Thank you very much for your response, Ryan. Sorry to keep bothering but, besides venues, are there any other places where bands can actually promote their music? (Bars, coffee shops, etc). Or these were considered in the "venues" category? Do you know if promoters/managers are open about supporting new acts? Or do you have to have amazing contacts in order to get their support? Thanks again and sorry for all the trouble. Cheers!', 'Reply To: Montreal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'reply-to-montreal-3', '', '', '2013-07-27 17:46:23', '2013-07-27 21:46:23', '', 456, 'http://stagebanter.ca/forums/reply/reply-to-montreal-3/', 3, 'reply', '', 0),
(467, 1, '2013-07-27 21:09:10', '2013-07-28 01:09:10', 'Hi Erick,\n\nNo problem.  I add all kinds of venues from cafes to big venues on StageBanter.  Although I haven''t had time to research and add every canadian venue, so don''t assume that the venues on here are the only ones possible, there might be others.  Promoters and other bands might be able to suggest some.\n\n\nSome venues are open to new acts and others less so, but there''s no harm in asking if they''ll have you.  Try to link up with local bands that might fit well with your band.\n\nRyan', 'Reply To: Montreal', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'reply-to-montreal-4', '', '', '2013-07-27 21:09:10', '2013-07-28 01:09:10', '', 456, 'http://stagebanter.ca/forums/reply/reply-to-montreal-4/', 4, 'reply', '', 0);
