(282, 'Against the Grain - Grass Roots Artistic Development Promotion\r\n\r\nCollective Concerts is the in-house exclusive talent buyer of the legendary Horseshoe Tavern.\r\nThey also produce and promote concerts at Lee''s Palace, Opera House, Phoenix, Sound Academy, Kool Haus and more\r\n\r\nOwners/Talent Buyers: \r\n\r\nCraig Laskey \r\ncraig@collectiveconcerts.com\r\nContact Craig from 1 - 9 pm\r\nphone: 416-598-0720\r\nfax: 416-598-2230\r\n\r\nJC (Jeff Cohen)\r\njc@collectiveconcerts.com\r\nATG Administration:\r\n\r\nDaria Ludwiczak \r\ndaria@collectiveconcerts.com\r\nContact Daria from noon - 8 pm\r\nphone: 416-598-0720\r\nfax: 416-598-2230\r\n\r\n\r\n	\r\nLegendary Artist Development Showcase Nites\r\n\r\n 	\r\nWe''ve created a series of SHOWCASE evenings....not dependant upon nor dictated by mainstream commercial radio, video, and rec co marketing, but which emphasizes the natural bond-experience between artist and night club fan - which is best nurtured in an intimate live concert setting... and can result in the building of a real street-level grassroots following...\r\n\r\nTuesday Nu Music Nites\r\n\r\nA NO COVER 6 year old weekly showcase series, sponsored by Canada''s highest profile modern rock radio station, 102.1 the Edge CFNY. Tuesdays are hosted by DJ BOOKIE, and feature cutting edge Nu Music from 9:45 to 1:00 am. The Series has featured the Toronto debuts of Tracey Bonham, Everclear, Ash, Catatonia, Semi-Sonic, Feul, Harvey Danger, Tonic, Candyskins, Local H, Sneaker Pimps, Hovercraft, Cree Summer, Jimmies Chicken Shack, Old 97''s, Robbie Fulks, Slobberbone, V-Roys, Dan Bern, Meredith Brooks, Katek Keineg, Flashing Lights, Goldfinger, Reel Big Fish, Mustard Plug, Nerfherder, Bloodhound Gang, Nada Surf, and hoards of then unknown Indie National Canadian Artists.....As it is always NO COVER, artist renumeration is minimal, but more importantly, we guarantee an turnout of 150-300, friendlier than anywhere staff and techs, free cold beer, draft, juice, & pop, and a receptive audience of resident music fans & industry...NMN is a superb first shoe introductory play for local and provincial alternative and indie artists...\r\n\r\nShoeless Mondays\r\n\r\nA NO COVER 3 year old weekly showcase series, featuring cutting non-alternative rock n pop from 9:45 to 12:30 am. The series has featured the likes of Coal Chamber, Tripping Daisy, and Hankdogs, but is where virtually every local Toronto area artist begins at The Shoe, before graduating to other nites...As it is always NO COVER, artist renumeration is a minumum $50.00, and cold beer, draft, juice, and pop...Shoeless is a non-pressure DIY breeding ground for future weekend local headliners...\r\n\r\nAmerican & International Touring Artists\r\n\r\nPlease have your agency and/or management contact ATG for avails!...We have a reputation for being thee place to see the breakout dates of WILCO, Ben Harper, ELVEZ! Son Volt, WHISKEYTOWN, Old 97''s, Amazing Royal Crowns, Jimmie Dale Gilmore, Kelly Willis....\r\n\r\nSo keep em coming, will ya....there isn''t a warmer, more artist friendly, international, home away from home, Canadian welcomer, ''it''s great to be in a band on the road despite the immigration hassle n freezing ice cold'' hassle free venue than the Shoe.\r\n\r\nAsk Golden Smog...they started their last tour here....Ask Jake Gold, Elliott Lefko, Frank Riley, Paul Goldman, Monterrey Penn, Ali and Tom at Billions Corp, Jim Romeo at Legends, Ralph James at Agency, Vinny and Jeff at SLF, RJ at Courage, Rob at Paguin, Paul Kahn at concerted...\r\n\r\nThe Shoe offers touring artists ''Better than Mercury Lounge'' artist take All 90% net door deals and the occasional USD Guarantee. We welcome and encourage co-promotes and work actively with House of Blues, Core, Flohill, Eggplant, 102.1 the Edge, rec co A&R-marketing directors...\r\n\r\nThe TRAGICALLY HIP, Watchmen, BLUE RODEO, BIG SUGAR, Amanda Marshall, GREAT BIG SEA, Stompin Tom, NEKO CASE, CHIXDIGGIT!, Smugglers, & SKYDIGGERS\r\n------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://www.horseshoetavern.com/bookings.htm">http://www.horseshoetavern.com/</a>\r\n\r\nTechnical Specs: <a href="http://www.horseshoetavern.com/tech_specs.htm">http://www.horseshoetavern.com/tech_specs.htm</a>'),
