(329, 'email: bookings@theblacksheepinn.com *Prices do not include taxes and/or service charges. Advanced tickets must be purchased at least 24 hours prior to the show. *Arrive at least 90 minutes prior for a *chance * at seating because seating is very limited. For busy shows, it is mostly standing, really. You need to know that we are a club venue, which means a mix of seating, standing, wandering around and dancing. *We are proudly a workingman''s jukejoint divebar tavern. We are in a dustly little Quebec village, north of Gatineau. Please do not expect a quaint inn, bistro, theatre, or hall. *Be sure to print your ticket or display your proof of purchase on your smartphone and bring it to blacksheep - it is your only proof of purchase. *Tickets sold at the door might be a few dollars more expensive than advanced tickets *All reservations expire at showtime. Limited seating, first-come, first-served. $1 surcharge on tickets sold at downtown locations... please support local, independent, small business!!\r\n\r\n------\r\nsource: <a href="http://tickets.theblacksheepinn.com/">http://tickets.theblacksheepinn.com/</a>'),
(347, 'We''re open every day from 8am - Midnight\r\n\r\nPhone: 604-254-1195\r\nTo book an event contact\r\nbooking@cafedeuxsoleils.com\r\nTo display your art contact\r\njeff@cafedeuxsoleils.com\r\n\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://www.cafedeuxsoleils.com/">http://www.cafedeuxsoleils.com/</a>'),
(365, 'If you or the act you represent is interested in performing at the Haven Social Club please contact Darrek Anderson at booking@thehavensocialclub.com. We typically book 3 – 4 months in advance. Seating capacity is 150, cabaret raked seating, table and bar service. The Haven has a full lounge menu and proudly serves Pharos Pizza, the best pizza in Western Canada. The Haven is a fully licensed venue with a wide assortment of tasty cocktails as well as high-quality wines and the usual beers and liquors.\r\n\r\nThe Haven is happy to work with outside promoters and to book private functions/private parties. Our room rental rates are very reasonable and we have world-class in-house catering available upon request. With a high-definition projector and 8’ screen, The Haven is also the perfect venue for video releases and movie screenings. Please contact Darrek Anderson at booking@thehavensocialclub.com for all booking matters. Please contact Darrek Anderson or Ryan Latta at info@thehavensocialclub.com regarding all promotional materials and inquiries.\r\n\r\nVisual artists:\r\nIf you are interested in displaying your collection or having a gallery show, contact Ryan Latta at ryan@thehavensocialclub.com. Exhibits are typically one month long and The Haven takes no commission for sales; all sales are directly through the artist. Art hanging and framing are the responsibility of the artist.\r\n\r\nIf you have just been confirmed with Darrek Anderson that your gig at the Haven is confirmed from our end please follow these 3 important steps:\r\n1. Please send booking confirmation to booking@thehavensocialclub.com stating you have read and understand the Haven’s booking policy, as explained below. Until you do this we do not consider the gig confirmed and may give the date to someone else, as our calendar fills up rapidly. Once you have sent this confirmation your email serves as a contract between you and the Haven binding both you and the Haven to the policy outlined here.\r\n2. Send the following show details to Darrek/Ryan at info@thehavensocialclub.com ( PLEASE send this all in one email if possible): \r\ni) hi-res band picture (at least 300 dpi)\r\nii) band bio\r\niii) a poster, if you’ve made one\r\niv) website links and any other pertinent web links for the band (Myspace etc)\r\n3. Send your stage plot and input list to James Murdoch at sound@thehavensocialclub.com and confirm sound check time with him, as per the details below. The Haven has a high end back line you are more than welcome to use (details below).\r\nBooking Policy\r\nThe Haven provides the following for the booked acts:\r\n\r\n*online and print promotion/advertisement of your show (see below for details)\r\n*professional sound technician (contact James Murdoch at sound@thehavensocialclub.com to coordinate sound tech requirements)\r\n*professional back line (see below for details) \r\n*quality sound system and lighting (see below for details)\r\n*greenroom\r\n*full bar and bartending/wait staff\r\n\r\nThe way the money works:\r\n\r\nBy playing at the Haven, you are basically renting out a high quality music and special events room for FREE, including a professional sound tech, back line. The Haven takes 100% of bar sales and the first $250.00 from ticket sales. The booked act keeps all the rest of the income from ticket sales, and 100% of their merchandise sales. Depending on what is charged for admission and how many people attend, it’s very realistic for a booked act to make between $1300.00 and $5400.00. Busy nights are a frequent occurrence at The Haven and artists are given the opportunity to make a good deal of money in a single evening. By being proactive and professional in the way they promote themselves, a band or artist can greatly increase their chance of making money. The Haven is an A-List room where music is given top priority, and its owner and staff take great care to ensure all musicians performing there have a great experience.\r\n\r\n3 Week Radius Clause:\r\n\r\nWe ask that if you are playing at the Haven you do not book another show 3 weeks before of afterward within a 100 km radius of Edmonton. This is to ensure your draw is not conflicting with any other venues in town. If you are a local band that just likes to play for fun every weekend in town the Haven is probably a place you would want to reserve for your CD release only, or some special occasion. We are open to making some exceptions to this rule, but we would ask that this be addressed PRIOR to confirming your booking with us.\r\n\r\nCancellation Policy:\r\n\r\nIf you need to cancel your gig booked at the Haven we require 3 or more weeks’ notice, as communicated via email to booking@thehavensocialclub.com. Failure to give this notice will mean we may still charge you a $200.00 deposit for the room.\r\n\r\nActs on the Bill:\r\n\r\nThere will normally be 2 artists per performance. How the door is allocated between the artist(s) can be one of two ways 1) an opening act and headliner, in which case the opener takes receive 30% of this profit, and the headliner takes 70%, or 2) a double bill, i which case the 2 acts take a 50/50 split of the door. The headliner will set the ticket price (minimum $10), or if you are sharing the bill we ask that you and the other act sort out what you’d like to charge (minimum $10). These 2 scenarios are guidelines to help you and exceptions can be made to these rules. If you have any questions or concerns regarding payout after the show, please contact Darrek at booking@thehavensocialclub.com PRIOR to the event.\r\n\r\nThe Haven’s Promotion and Advertising for Booked Acts:\r\n\r\nShow submitted to all local print media listings one – two weeks prior to show date\r\nFeature show poster on the Haven’s Homepage the week of the show, list show and show details on the Haven’s calendar, and lists the artist’s bio and photos on the Haven’s website\r\nList show on the Haven’s Myspace and Facebook sites\r\nSend an email to our (very large) email list of Haven members regardingthe show (in our bi-weekly newletter)\r\nOptional: post one song you agree to make downloadable to us on the Haven’s Myspace, 1–2 weeks leading up to your show. Please notify us at booking@thehavensocialclub.com if you wish to do this, and when the song will be downloadable, so we can upload it to our site. Once your show is over we will be deleting the song to make room for the next upcoming acts.\r\nAdvance ticket sales online (YEG Live) and in the venue.\r\nOnce your show has been confirmed, you will receive The Haven’s Artist Info Package. This document contains all the information necessary for your show. Please read through it carefully and contact the appropriate member of The Haven staff if you have any questions.\r\n\r\nWe’ve included some of the more pertinent details from our Artist Information Package below.\r\n\r\nSound Check and Set Times:\r\n\r\nWe ask that the bands load in for 7:45pm. Please load through the back door, accessible from the back alley where there is ample parking. Sound check starts at 7:45pm sharp and concludes at 8:30pm. If you have any questions regarding sound check, please contact James Murdoch at sound@thehavensocialclub.com.\r\n\r\nThe Haven Back Line:\r\n\r\nGuitar Amps\r\nFender Super Reverb\r\nFender Twin\r\n\r\nBass Amp\r\nTraynor Dynabass 200T (2×10” Combo)\r\n\r\nKeyboard & Amp\r\nKorg Triton Extreme\r\n\r\nDrums\r\nSonor Delight 20”, 10”, 12”, 13”, 14”, 16” \r\nGretch Jazz 18” Kit, 12”, 14”\r\nmic’d and ready to go\r\n\r\nMusic stands available\r\n\r\nThe Haven PA\r\n\r\nFront Of House\r\n1x Allen & Heath – GL2400–24-4 mixing console\r\nmore info\r\n\r\n1x Rapco-24×4Ch 100Ft Snake (Will eventually be replaced by a Rapco split\r\nin the event we require a monitor console to be brought in)\r\n\r\n2x KV2-EX12T Speakers\r\nmore info\r\n\r\n2x KV2-KX1.5 Subwoofers\r\nmore info\r\n\r\nMonitors\r\n4x Yamaha-MSR400\r\nmore info\r\n\r\nEffects\r\nTC Electronics M0neXL or t\r\nmore info\r\n\r\nDBX1074 (more info), \r\nDBX1046 (more info)\r\n\r\nMicrophones\r\nAs for mics there will be Shure 58s for vocals, E604s for the drums and a Shure-Beta52 for the kick, rode NT5s for Hi-Hats/overheads, Shure-Beta57A for Guitars and misc instruments, Radial-JDImk3 or Shure Beta52 for Bass Guitar\r\n\r\nThanks in advance for playing at the Haven, we look forward to seeing and hearing you.\r\n\r\n------------------------------------\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://thehavensocialclub.com/booking/">http://thehavensocialclub.com/booking/</a>'),
(426, 'Jerry Hong / Bookings \r\nQueens Hotel 34 Victoria Crescent Nanaimo\r\nBC, V9R 5B8 \r\njerry@thequeens.ca \r\nTHE BEST WAY TO CONTACT JOEL IS BY EMAIL!!! \r\n\r\nYOU NEED TO SEND US: A copy of your CD / bio\r\n/ references / realistic plan for marketing \r\n\r\nTHE ROOM: 200 seats / full sound system \r\nw/engineer.\r\n3 x 45 min sets \r\nno rooms at venue \r\n\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://thequeens.ca/contact.htm">http://thequeens.ca/contact.htm</a>'),
(455, '\r\nIf you’d like to book an event for private or public use, please email us at corinne@riotheatre.ca\r\n\r\nOur stage size is 40 feet wide and 20 feet deep with a newly renovated greenroom (private bathroom, built in heaters and internet) for performers.  The theatre has 420 seats, including a balcony section. There are few – if any – venues in the city with the intimacy and acoustics like the Rio. Concerts here are unforgettable. If you are renting the theatre for your movie premiere or film festival our recently installed HD digital projector is the same quality that all the major multiplexes use. Our concession stand is set up to be licensed for serving alcohol on special events.  Our friendly staff will make you feel like you are at home and we pride ourselves to help make your event a success.\r\n\r\nRates vary depending on dates and times. click to know more.\r\n\r\nThis is what the Rio provides when you rent\r\n\r\n1. Cinema sound system is for films and recorded music only.\r\n2. One manager/tech person (Rio equipment) plus one box office person\r\n3. Concession/bar service\r\n4. One security guard if needed\r\n\r\nEQUIPMENT\r\n\r\n35mm projector & state of the art digital projector,  two microphones plus an upright piano and tables for merch.\r\n\r\nNEWLY INSTALLED LIGHTING: 26 LED par cans; 6 lekos spotlights (fixed position); 1 follow spot.\r\n\r\n*A  sound system is available from Rock Shop at extra cost.  Ranges from $200-$1,000 depending on what is required*\r\n\r\nIf you have an event, the Rio can hold it. Along with our stunning cinematic and concert presentation the Rio has hosted a variety of events: fashion shows, comedy shows, award galas, graduations, film shoots and weddings to name a few, but, the possibilities do not end there. Let us know what you need.\r\n\r\n____________\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://riotheatre.ca/bookings/">http://riotheatre.ca/bookings/</a>'),
(479, 'How To Book A Show At Phog\r\n\r\nE-mail Tom Lucier at phoglounge@gmail.com with several potential dates that you’re hoping to book. Your first choice may not be available\r\n\r\nIn the event that the best night for your gig is booked, you can search the line-ups upcoming on www.phoglounge.com and check if you fit any shows happening in the next two months.\r\n\r\nThere are hyperlinks to all the performers so you can listen and check if your sound works with the show already booked.\r\n\r\nAnything with only two bands, or a TBA, potentially has room for an opening set. Mostly though…we’d prefer one out of town band and one local…or just a couple of locals.\r\n\r\nThe best way to book a show is to have a local (or two) already slated to join you on the show. This is the simplest set-up for Phog to begin promoting the show quickly instead of hunting for local bands available for your show.\r\n\r\nFor more info about what happens after you book a show, read <a href="http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/">“FAQs for Bands Booked at Phog”.</a>\r\n\r\n------------------------\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/">http://phoglounge.com/phog-booking-information/</a>\r\n\r\n'),
(544, 'The TRANZAC’s club facilities are available for rental by the general public.\r\n\r\nWe are conveniently located just south of Bloor Street West between the Bathurst and Spadina subway stations offering easy access to the Bloor-Danforth and University-Spadina subway lines.\r\n\r\nThe Tranzac is one block east of a large municipal parking lot off of Lippincott and onsite parking can be made available for setup and tear down if required.\r\n\r\nWe are located in the heart of the vibrant and historic Annex neighbourhood and within walking distance of many wonderful shops, restaurants and the University of Toronto.\r\n\r\nOur facilities can accommodate meetings of 15 to 150 people. Our Main Hall performance space features a full PA and lighting system and a 7-meter deep stage.\r\n\r\nRecently the Main Hall has been packed for music festivals, film festivals, plays, book launchs, CD launches and other concerts and as well as private events such as parties, Bar Mitzvahs, and craft shows.\r\n\r\nTo inquire about rentals, please email booking@tranzac.org, or call (416) 923-8137.\r\n\r\nAre you emerging local musician about to put out an album ? Learn more about our <a href="http://www.tranzac.org/emergingmusicseries/">Tranzac Emerging Local Music Series</a> for information about subsidized rentals.\r\n\r\n--------------\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://www.tranzac.org/rentals/">http://www.tranzac.org/rentals/</a>\r\n'),
(559, 'Many bands/performers want to play ZAPHOD’s but we obviously can’t accommodate everyone that sends us their press package.\r\n\r\nCan you remember the last time YOU plunked down your hard-earned dineros/pesetas/pounds/dollars to see a band? Chances are it was a band you heard on the radio, read about, saw their video, or knew about in some way. That’s how audiences generally decide what they want to see…so if you are an unknown act, chances are the audience isn’t going to show up just because you’re playing, even if it is at Ottawa’s most credible live music club.\r\n\r\nIf audiences don’t show up, the band makes no money, the staff makes no money, the club makes no money. If that happens often enough, the club will eventually close and there will be one less place to see live music and for bands to play. Keep this in mind when you make the effort to send us your kit.\r\n\r\nMany performers are rejected, not because they aren’t talented, but because they are not appropriate for the club presently. We don’t want you to waste your hard-earned money on CDs, demos, glossys, posters, postage, couriers, only to have them rejected.\r\n\r\nHaving said all that, good luck in your endeavours.\r\n\r\nSend an email, including your web site link, MySpace link and MP3 links to: zaphodsbooking@gmail.com with “Booking a show at Zaphod’s” in the subject line. Be clear, concise and professional.\r\n\r\nWhen you do get booked, it’s your responsibility to ensure a good turnout. Zaphod’s capacity is 250. If you can’t convince enough people that you’re as good as you say you are, we can’t do much for you. So its incumbent on you to have a reasonable turnout if you expect to be re-booked. Make sure you call all your friends, relatives and acquaintances. Poster the streets. Hand out flyers. Call up the media and tell your story. A good turnout = A good feeling all around.\r\n\r\nAll artists / promoters / street-poster-teams should read this important information: <a href="http://zaphods.ca/?page_id=147">Postering Etiquette</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n_________\r\nsource:<a href="http://zaphods.ca/?page_id=24">http://zaphods.ca/?page_id=24</a>'),
(606, 'FAQ''s\r\n\r\nplease read carefully.\r\n\r\nBefore you call and email me... I suggest you check the Calendar... if the date you are looking for already has bands announced... then you''ll have to find another date to pass through Sudbury.\r\n\r\nWhere are you? The Townehouse Tavern, 206 Elgin St., Sudbury, Ontario, Canada, P3E 3N5\r\n\r\nWhat do you book? ... easier to tell you what we don''t book... we DON''T book bands that perform top 40 covers or classic rock covers (there''s a ton of other bars that do it... we''re happy to be unique in our community). We DON''T book bands that play NEW COUNTRY. We don''t have a DJ night. We have live music every night. We love Reggae, Ska, Punk, World, Soul, Funk, Garage, Indie Rock and Surf music... we also like rock, folk, heavy metal, jazz, blues,\r\n\r\nWhat do you do during the week? From Sunday to Wednesday we generally have acoustic solo acts perform. No soundman. No Doorman. No Cover charge. We are basically a neighbourhood pub during the week and have worldclass bands every weekend. If you happen to have a fast rising single on rock radio across the country... we may do a weekday show for you. Otherwise... try to route through here on a weekend.\r\n\r\nCan we make an exception this time? Stop asking the question. If we have turned you down for a show then come up with another date that fits into the booking scheme.\r\n\r\nWho books the bar? ... Paul Loewenberg is the booker. email is on this page. I am at the bar every day but often only for a short time while I run in and out doing things. If you call the bar, they will give you my email address. EMAIL IS BEST.\r\n\r\nI called the bar, they gave me your phone number?... I book the bar and run the site, Facebook and MySpace stuff from home...they will give you my cel phone number... feel free to call me during reasonable business hours. Not on Sundays.\r\n\r\nI emailed, I called - you still haven''t got back to me? ... Between the Townehouse and the Festival, I get 500-700 emails each week. I respond to every email that I believe will result in a booking. If I haven''t gotten back to you it is clearly because you have asked for a date that is NOT AVAILABLE.\r\n\r\nThe Townehouse responded saying the date was full... should I email back offering my band as an opener? ... NO. if we need an opening band, I''ll ask when you give the date. We don''t need a fourth band on the bill. We don''t need you to play for free. You are better than that. If the bar is booked, go find yourself another gig and call us next time you''ll be passing through Sudbury. We always make more of an effort for bands that are going to be coming through here more often.\r\n\r\nWhere will my band stay when in Sudbury? ... The Townehouse has a bandhouse for the touring folks. There are 2 queens, a double, a single, a fold out couch, 2 more couches, a shower, TV, a private entrance. Pictures are HERE. The bandroom is kept clean... sheets are washed and changed everytime a band uses the room. This is not a party room, this is a living area for you... bands that leave bad messes don''t get invited back.\r\n\r\nIf you want to inquire about getting your band booked... send your CD, email a link to your website, vital info, routing times, electronic press kit, etc. and we''ll get back to you.    paul@thetownehouse.com\r\n\r\nare you having problems viewing my site?    info@thetownehouse.com\r\n\r\ngeneral inquiries?    paul@thetownehouse.com\r\n\r\n\r\n--------------\r\n\r\nsource: <a href="http://www.thetownehouse.com/contact_page.htm">http://www.thetownehouse.com/contact_page.htm</a>'),
(656, 'To apply for a music/performance/workshop/one-time event send us an email with your request.\r\n\r\nFee: $50/night\r\nThis includes:\r\n\r\n- The space\r\n- PA on site\r\n- Facebook event\r\n\r\nPlease note, The Artel does not promote the event other than through facebook and website. Music ends by 11pm for a happy rapport with neighbours.\r\n'),
(690, 'For booking info **PLEASE** send all mail to solar.townsATgmail.com and we will get back to you as soon as possible, **DO NOT contact the hotel directly** \r\n\r\n\r\nSource:<a href="http://www.myspace.com/canmorehotel">http://www.myspace.com/canmorehotel</a>'),
(719, 'Artist Booking\r\nContact Art Szabo - Talent Buyer\r\n(780)428-1099 or (780)966 - 6166\r\n\r\nLocal Booking - Lyndsay Burnett - Assistant Talent Buyer\r\n(780)428-1099 or (780)244-3731\r\n\r\nPlease send Phone Number (cell only), all Links and any artwork logo etc with email for booking inquiries. Emails without this info will be deleted and probably not answered. SERIOUS INQUIRIES ONLY\r\n\r\nart@starliteroom.ca\r\n\r\nDJ Bookings:\r\nNick Samalack\r\n(780) 428-1099\r\n\r\nnick@starliteroom.ca\r\n\r\n\r\nTech Information\r\nContact Mike Noga\r\n(780) 428-1099\r\n\r\nmikenoga@gmail.com\r\n\r\n------------------\r\n\r\nSource:<a href="http://www.starliteroom.ca/booking.php">http://www.starliteroom.ca/booking.php</a>\r\n'),
