(988, 'Monday nights is Chick Picken Mondays, female singer song writers booking gern@uswm.ca\r\nTuesday Night open mic.\r\nWednesday Might is Jazz night, open jam following house band\r\nThursday Night is Old Tyme Cercle Jam, Old Tyme, Blue Grass, and Country\r\nFriday and Saturday Nights varried book at info@grumpybar.ca\r\n'),
(1063, 'If you are interested in booking a show at the Company House, we accept email proposals only.  Please do not call without first sending us an email with your information and links to your website or myspace page. The Company House is first and foremost a live music venue.  We’re a listening room primarily presenting singer songwriters. We present any genre of music except punk, hard core, and indie rock (with the rare exception). There are several bars in the Halifax area who present these types of music that a simple google search will reveal. Please do not send requests if your band fits into one of those genres.\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://www.thecompanyhouse.ca/html/contact_us.html>http://www.thecompanyhouse.ca/html/contact_us.html</a>'),
(1075, 'If you are interested in performing at Struts Gallery & Faucet Media Arts Centre please contact our Live Music Coordinator at strutsmusic@gmail.com.\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://strutsgallery.ca/concerts.htm">http://strutsgallery.ca/concerts.htm</a>'),
(1110, 'Use the form at <a href="http://solsticecafe.ca/contact/performing">http://solsticecafe.ca/contact/performing</a>\r\n\r\nsolstice café offers a beautiful venue to play your music, speak your poetry, or perform your piece.  if you’re touring in the area and you feel you may have a draw of fans in Victoria, please fill in the form below, in the meantime, here are some things you should know…\r\n\r\nwe’re not licensed, and all shows are all-ages.\r\nour seating capacity is up to almost 100 people.\r\nperformers are responsible for promotion of the event, but we will put up show posters that you provide us in the cafe, and add show details to our online accounts (such as Twitter, FaceBook & MySpace).\r\nperformers can sell CDs and other merchandise without a commission charge.\r\nperformers recieve a $10 tab each, up to $50 on any given show night.\r\n\r\n'),
(1121, 'For info or bookings, please email at www.myspace.com/apollobar or on Facebook(The Apollo Bar or Sheila Rock)or at theapollobar@gmail.com.\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://www.myspace.com/apollobar">http://www.myspace.com/apollobar</a>'),
(1186, 'Wine-Ohs'' Cellar is a premier live music room featuring roots, blues, folk, jazz, and some genres in between. Interested artists/agents can contact bookings@wine-ohs.com with EPKs and available dates.\r\n\r\nSource: <a href="http://wine-ohs.com/events">http://wine-ohs.com/events</a>'),
(1198, 'If you have any questions or are interested in playing the Elevation Room please email:\r\n\r\nJoe Gurba, Venue Manager - er@transcendcoffee.com\r\n\r\n\r\nSource:<a href="http://elevationroom.com/">http://elevationroom.com/</a>'),
(1211, 'POUR VENIR JOUER AU ZARICOT, CONTACTEZ  JOËLLE TURCOTTE PAR COURRIEL AU JOELLE@LEZARICOT.COM\r\n\r\nVous devez fournir :\r\n\r\n- Un démo (liens utiles vers myspace, bandcamp, etc)\r\n- Une brève biographie du groupe\r\n- La date ou la période désirée\r\n\r\nDESCRIPTIF DE L’ÉQUIPEMENT:\r\n\r\n• 2x JBL PRX535 (Speakers)\r\n• 2x JBL PRX718S (Subs)\r\n• 2x JBL MRX512 (Delay) avec ampli Crown XTI2002\r\n• 1x DBX Drive Rack PA\r\n• 1x Console Midas Venice F 32\r\n• 1x Presonus ACP88 (Compresseur 8 lignes)\r\n• 1x TC Electronic M1 (FX)\r\n• 4x DBX 231 Graphic EQ\r\n• 4x JBL MRX512 (Moniteurs)\r\n• 2x Crown CE 1000 (Amplis Moniteurs)\r\n\r\n• 4x Shure SM58\r\n• 4x Shure SM57\r\n• 1x Shure Beta57A\r\n• 1x Shure Beta91A\r\n• 1x Apex Drums Kit (1x Kick, 1x Snare, 1x Tom, 1x Floor)\r\n• 2x Sennheiser Overhead\r\n• 5x DI Box\r\n\r\n• Pieds de micros (Grands et petits)\r\n• Filage XLR\r\n\r\nDIRECTEUR TECHNIQUE:\r\n\r\nChristophe Marais\r\n\r\ninfo@studios57.com\r\n\r\n\r\nSource<a href="http://www.lezaricot.com/booking">http://www.lezaricot.com/booking</a>'),
